    "Name": "Conjurer",
    "Details": "The Conjurer, designated the Hellhound by the IS, is a medium to short range fighter. The mech is, for all intents and purposes, a Wolverine IIC however the Clans would not be willing to name a mech after Clan Wolverine, and so it was renamed. As a second line mech, most variants use a standard engine, but do mount an endo-steel chassis for reduced weight. This variant, however, also uses an extra-light engine to save as much weight as possible for weaponry. Mounting a quartet of heavy medium lasers, a medium pulse laser and twin Stream SRM-6s, this mech pushes the 14 double heatsinks well past their endurance. For anti-infantry work it also mounts two light machine guns.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
